<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1903-01-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1903-01-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="399" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d399">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Tower</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1903-01-06"><hi rend="italic">January 6,
                                1903</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Hay advises Mr. Tower of the receipt of the British reply accepting
                            the negotiation if Venezuela assents to conditions imposed by Great
                            Britain, and appointing the British ambassador to confer with Mr. Bowen
                            in Washington.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>